After the last release, Travis tests on all PRs failed for a week until #4162 was merged. This PR fixes #4166 making our tests more flexible to prevent this problem in the future.

@ohemorange, would you feel comfortable reviewing this? I'd like to get this in by Wednesday to prevent everyone's PRs from breaking again.

EDIT: I forgot to mention I tested this against the `0.10.x` branch as you can see [here](https://travis-ci.org/certbot/certbot/jobs/205909523).

As far as I can tell, master has stopped building correctly due to a dependency update (related to [this](https://github.com/DefinitelyTyped/DefinitelyTyped/issues/17239)?). This is (probably) only visible off a fresh clone, or at least removing the node_modules in *jupyter-widgets-controls*. It also occurred on PR #1410.

I think this is due to an update in the type defintions for JQuery. The module definition now reads:

```typescript
declare module 'jquery' {
    export = factory;
}

declare function factory(window: Window, noGlobal?: boolean): JQueryStatic;

declare const $: JQueryStatic;
```

This means that the only ways of importing jquery are:

```typescript
const $ = require('jquery') // uses the exported module 'jquery'
import 'jquery' // uses the global exports, which injects $ into the global namespace
```

In particular, we were importing jQuery using `import * as $ from 'jquery'`, which is now not allowed.

This is still fairly broken on Travis.
